      "Repair plan to be submitted to BSEE pipeline division for approval"
    ],
    "summary": "On December 2, 2024, at approximately 0830 hours, a gas release was discovered from subsea flowline pipeline segment 10688 at VK 989 Platform A during pressure testing of a newly replaced Subsea Control Module (SCM) pod. The gas release was detected by control room operators during testing, confirmed by ROV investigation showing gas bubbles at a 90-degree bend in the flowline. The operator immediately suspended testing and isolated the pipeline segment. The suspected cause is corrosion at a previous field repair weld that may have had imperfections. Repair options include installing an engineered clamp or replacing the damaged section with flexible pipe.",
    "recommendations": [
      "BSEE New Orleans District has no recommendations for Office of Incident Investigations at this time"
